---
By: James Allen
Locus:
  Page: 302
  Verse: 12
Tags:
  - Loneliness
---
When one understands that the great things of the world and of life consist
of a combination of small things, and that without this aggregation of
small things the great things would be nonexistent, then he begins to pay
careful attention to those things which he formerly regarded as
insignificant.
